Senate Resolution 78
By: Senators Watson of the 1st, Hickman of the 4th, Hodges of the 3rd, Kennedy of the 18th,
Burns of the 23rd and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Kathy Hogan Trocheck, who is also recognized
2 internationally under the pen name Mary Kay Andrews; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Mary Kay Andrews earned a Bachelor of Arts in journalism from the University
4 of Georgia and embarked on a 14-year career as a reporter at newspapers such as The
5 Savannah Morning News, The Marietta Journal, and The Atlanta Journal-Constitution
6 before leaving journalism in 1991 to write fiction; and
7 WHEREAS, Mary Kay Andrews is the New York Times bestselling author of 30 novels,
8 including The Homewreckers; The Santa Suit; The Newcomer; Hello, Summer; Sunset Beach;
9 The High Tide Club; The Weekenders; Beach Town; Save the Date; Ladies' Night; Christmas
10 Bliss; Spring Fever; Summer Rental; The Fixer Upper; Deep Dish; Blue Christmas;
11 Savannah Breeze; Hissy Fit; Little Bitty Lies; and Savannah Blues, as well as one cookbook,
12 The Beach House Cookbook; and
13 WHEREAS, after her first novel, Every Crooked Nanny, was published in 1992 by
14 HarperCollins, she went on to write ten critically acclaimed mysteries under her real name,
15 Kathy Hogan Trocheck; and
